1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,971
Just a few weeks ago, a friend who is an official with a state highway department in a Midwestern state related a mountain-moving experience to me.

2
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:24,291
Last month, my friend began, our department sent notices to a number of engineering companies that we were authorized to retain some firm to design eight bridges as part of our highway building program.

3
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:28,370
The bridges were to be built at a cost of five million dollars.

4
00:00:28,560 --> 00:00:35,570
The engineering firm selected would get a four percent commission or two hundred thousand dollars for its design work.

5
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,570
I talked with twenty-one engineering firms about this.

6
00:00:39,841 --> 00:00:43,891
The four largest decided right away to submit proposals.

7
00:00:44,080 --> 00:00:49,651
The other seventeen companies were small, having only three to seven engineers each.

8
00:00:49,921 --> 00:00:54,291
The size of the project scared off sixteen of these seventeen.

9
00:00:54,560 --> 00:01:00,211
They went over the project, shook their heads, and said, in effect, it's too big for us.

10
00:01:00,401 --> 00:01:04,370
I wish I thought we could handle it, but it's no use even trying.

11
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:10,930
But one of these small firms, a company with only three engineers, studied the plans and said,

12
00:01:11,041 --> 00:01:13,731
we can do it, we'll submit a proposal.

13
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,531
They did, and they got the job.

14
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:20,451
Those who believe they can move mountains, do.

15
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:23,010
Those who believe they can't, cannot.

16
00:01:23,361 --> 00:01:26,051
Belief triggers the power to do.

